Fixed Units:

Pixels (px):

Category: Fixed
Usage: Absolute unit, provides a fixed size regardless of the context.
Points (pt):

Category: Fixed
Usage: Absolute unit commonly used in print styling, 1pt is equal to 1/72 inch.
Picas (pc):

Category: Fixed
Usage: Rarely used, 1pc is equal to 12 points.
Millimeters (mm):

Category: Fixed
Usage: Absolute unit representing a fixed size in millimeters.
Inches (in):

Category: Fixed
Usage: Absolute unit representing a fixed size in inches.
Relative Units:

Em (em):

Category: Relative
Usage: Relative unit, size is based on the font-size of the parent or the element itself.
Rem (rem):

Category: Relative
Usage: Relative unit, size is based on the font-size of the root (usually the <html>) element.
Percentage (%):

Category: Relative
Usage: Relative unit, size is a percentage of the parent element.
Viewport Width (vw) and Viewport Height (vh):

Category: Relative
Usage: Relative unit, size is a percentage of the viewport width or height.
Viewport Minimum (vmin) and Viewport Maximum (vmax):

Category: Relative
Usage: Relative unit, vmin is based on the smaller of the viewport's height and width, and vmax is based on the larger.


-----------------------------------------------
Code:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./Demo.css">
</head>
<body>


    <div id="Main">
        Hello
    </div>

  
</body>
</html>

* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

body {
  background-color: rgb(25, 25, 25);
  color: white;
  font-family: sans-serif;
  background-color: rgb(223, 222, 222);
}



#Main
{
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: 10pc auto;
    height: 200px;

    width: 25vmin;
    font-size: 2vmin;

    background-color: teal;
}
